==English==
===Verb form===
'''arsed'''

#(''British vulgar slang'') [[Bothered]] (as in '''can't be bothered to...''').
#:''I can't be arsed to get out of bed today.''
#:''We asked John if he wanted to come down the pub with us, but he couldn't be arsed.''

===Usage note===
*This word is used only in expressions of the form ''noun'' or ''pronoun'' + '''can't be arsed''' and ''noun'' or ''pronoun'' + '''couldn't be arsed'''.  The form *'''not be able to be arsed''' is not used.